    return Task.FromResult(httpWebResponse);
Should fix your error, however it will not make it truly async as no async method is being called within Smethod_1 and Smethod_1 lacks 
      
     public async Task&lt;string&gt; Smethod_1

As Neil noted in the comments, `Smethod_1` is returning a `HttpWebResponse`, but the method is declared as returning a `Task&lt;string&gt;`. The error message is telling you that `HttpWebResponse` cannot be implicitly converted to a `Task`.

Changing the declaration of `Smethod_1` to return a `Task&lt;HttpWebResponse&gt;`, and returning `return Task.FromResult(httpWebResponse)` as noted by jondow&#39;s answer, should correct the error you&#39;re seeing now. But, then you&#39;ll get a compiler error in `Smethod0` because you&#39;re calling `GetResponseStream` on the result of `Smethod_1`... which returns a `Task&lt;HttpWebResponse&gt;` and not just a `HttpWebResponse`. `Task&lt;HttpWebResponse&gt;` does not have a method called `GetResponseStream`.

You need to `await` the `Task` returned by `Smethod_1` in order to get the `HttpWebResponse`. In order to do that, you need to make `Smethod0` `async`.

```lang-csharp
public async Task&lt;string&gt; Smethod0(HttpWebRequest httpWebRequest0)
