If I&#39;m correct you want something similar to `componentDidMount` life-cycle method.
The way to do that is
```javascript
function MyComponent(props){
    useEffect(()=&gt;{
        // do stuff here...
    }, []) // &lt;-- empty dependency array
    return &lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
}
```

To under stand what&#39;s happening you&#39;ll need to understand how the useEffect hooks works.
Using the useEffect hook without any dependencies will trigger the effect every time some state or prop changes and causes a re-render.
but if we pass an empty array as dependency it will be as the effect not depended on any thing else, so it will only trigger when the component mounts.

